Let me analyze the main target image and provide a solution:

- The structure consists of green rectangular blocks and orange triangular/cylindrical blocks
- It has a central orange cylindrical column with green rectangular blocks on either side
- There are 3 orange triangular blocks creating a roof-like structure
- The structure is symmetrical

Block count and types needed:
- 4 green rectangular blocks (vertical orientation)
- 1 orange cylindrical block (vertical)
- 3 orange triangular blocks in different orientations

{

Step6: Move block with index 12

The assembly process:
1-2. Place two vertical green blocks (index 3) on the left side
3-4. Place two vertical green blocks (index 4) on the right side
5. Place the vertical orange cylinder (index 6) in the center
6-8. Add the three orange triangular blocks (indices 12, 14, and 15) as the roof elements

This will create the symmetrical structure shown in the target image, with the correct orientation of all blocks.
